      <div type="description" n="monument">
        <head>Description of Monument</head>
        <p>Left side, with upper and lower edges surviving, of a
rectangular <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">panel</rs> (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.27</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">0.265</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.03</measure>).</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="text">
        <head>Description of Text</head>
        <p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> on the face, which is polished, and has been
prepared with a lightly-cut grid, within which the letters are cut,
one letter in each square.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="letters">
        <head>Description of Letters</head>
        <p>Irregular but clear, av. <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.025</measure>; <term>epsilon</term> is both lunate (ll. 2, 3)
and square (ll. 4, 5). Two dots for stop, 1.4.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="date">
        <head>Date</head>
        <p><date exact="none" cert="low" notBefore="0401" notAfter="0600">Fifth or sixth century</date> (content, metre).</p>
      </div>

